WEBVTT

00:02.436 --> 00:03.802
Ohh, yeah!

00:03.804 --> 00:06.472
♪ Powerpuff Girls
fighting crime ♪

00:06.474 --> 00:09.108
♪ To save the world
before bedtime ♪

00:09.110 --> 00:11.543
♪ Here's the time to shine
when you're fighting crime ♪

00:11.545 --> 00:13.312
♪ Power it up ♪
♪ Who's got the power? ♪

00:13.314 --> 00:14.780
♪ We got the power ♪

00:14.782 --> 00:16.982
♪ Breaking through the wall,
gonna do it all ♪

00:16.984 --> 00:19.184
♪ We don't quit ♪
♪ Who's got the power? ♪

00:19.186 --> 00:20.819
♪ We got the power ♪

00:20.821 --> 00:23.155
Oh! Yeah!

00:23.157 --> 00:26.458
♪♪

00:29.397 --> 00:34.133
[ Rock music playing ]

00:34.135 --> 00:35.701
Whoo!

00:35.703 --> 00:40.039
[ Grunting ]

00:40.041 --> 00:41.306
Yeesh!
Ugh.

00:41.308 --> 00:43.042
Buttercup,
that's the third guitar

00:43.044 --> 00:44.376
you've smashed this month.

00:44.378 --> 00:45.978
If you keep smashing
your guitars,

00:45.980 --> 00:47.980
we'll never win the Battle of
the Band-Aids tomorrow.

00:47.982 --> 00:52.351
Ugh! For the last time, Bubbles,
it's Battle of the Bands,

00:52.353 --> 00:54.720
not Battle of the Band-Aids.

00:54.722 --> 00:58.023
Guys, relax.
I'll get it fixed.

00:58.025 --> 00:59.358
I got a guy.

00:59.360 --> 01:01.360
Yo, Steve!
I need a new guitar.

01:01.362 --> 01:03.262
This one's faulty.

01:03.264 --> 01:04.830
[ Twangs ]

01:04.832 --> 01:06.432
Sorry, kid, no dice.

01:06.434 --> 01:10.402
You made the no exchange
Wall of Shame.

01:10.404 --> 01:13.439
You can't just keep smashing
your guitars.

01:13.441 --> 01:16.241
Come on!
Smashing guitars is, like,

01:16.243 --> 01:19.445
<i> the</i> most important part
of<i> being</i> a rock star!

01:19.447 --> 01:21.847
What about Thrash?!

01:21.849 --> 01:23.916
♪ Thrash ♪

01:23.918 --> 01:25.784
She's the most metal,
wicked rock star

01:25.786 --> 01:27.786
that ever shredded
the audiosphere.

01:27.788 --> 01:30.856
She smashed every guitar
she's ever played!

01:30.858 --> 01:34.526
Even the ones
that weren't hers!

01:34.528 --> 01:39.198
She was a rock god!

01:39.200 --> 01:41.366
I still can't help you, kid.

01:41.368 --> 01:44.703
But the Battle of the Bands
is tomorrow!

01:44.705 --> 01:45.771
Ugh!

01:45.773 --> 01:47.706
I would give anything --
<i> anything --</i>

01:47.708 --> 01:51.677
for the chance
to be a rock god!

01:52.713 --> 01:56.648
Okay, kid.
I'll make you a deal.

01:56.650 --> 01:57.950
You will?!

01:57.952 --> 02:01.019
Yeah. Check this out.

02:03.557 --> 02:06.658
♪ Totally epic ♪

02:06.660 --> 02:08.127
Whoa!

02:08.129 --> 02:10.629
Yeah, "whoa" is right.

02:10.631 --> 02:14.066
It's a solid emerald
flying-V guitar,

02:14.068 --> 02:19.471
smelted together from a thousand
years of pure heavy metal.

02:19.473 --> 02:22.574
And it's super tiny, so it's
pretty much made for you.

02:22.576 --> 02:26.078
That's the most metal thing
I've ever seen.

02:26.080 --> 02:27.246
You want it?

02:27.248 --> 02:28.514
Heck, yeah!

02:28.516 --> 02:30.082
Hold on there, rock star.

02:30.084 --> 02:32.084
This guitar comes at a cost.

02:32.086 --> 02:36.755
If I give it to you, you will
owe something to me.

02:36.757 --> 02:38.257
Cool.

02:38.259 --> 02:42.094
It may come at a time and in
a way that you shall most dread.

02:42.096 --> 02:43.362
Ya-huh.

02:43.364 --> 02:45.697
So you may want to
think about it.

02:45.699 --> 02:47.032
Meh.

02:47.034 --> 02:48.800
It could come at any time!

02:48.802 --> 02:50.102
Sure.

02:50.104 --> 02:51.470
Like tomorrow.

02:51.472 --> 02:53.639
[ Snoring ]

02:53.641 --> 02:56.775
At the Battle of the Bands.

02:56.777 --> 02:58.544
Dude,
are you still talking?

02:58.546 --> 03:00.946
You're wasting valuable
shredding time!

03:00.948 --> 03:02.314
Just checking.

03:02.316 --> 03:03.782
Sweet.

03:03.784 --> 03:05.117
All right.

03:05.119 --> 03:08.620
With the power vested in me
by Steve's pawn shop,

03:08.622 --> 03:13.158
we must seal the deal with
the handshake of thrashitude.

03:13.160 --> 03:14.893
A G chord!

03:14.895 --> 03:17.029
Both: ♪ G chord ♪
[ Plays chord ]

03:17.031 --> 03:18.330
[ Growls ]

03:18.332 --> 03:19.731
♪♪

03:19.733 --> 03:23.168
So you're saying that you got
that guitar for free?

03:23.170 --> 03:25.504
Yup!
No strings attached?

03:25.506 --> 03:27.506
Nah, just the ones that came
with the guitar.

03:27.508 --> 03:30.876
What lame-brain would give you
a free guitar?

03:30.878 --> 03:32.477
That guy!

03:32.479 --> 03:34.079
♪ That guy ♪

03:34.081 --> 03:37.316
Okay, this light checks out!
[ Wheels squeaking ]

03:37.318 --> 03:39.384
Hey, Buttercup!

03:39.386 --> 03:40.752
Yo, Steve!

03:40.754 --> 03:42.921
You come to watch
the Battle of the Bands?

03:42.923 --> 03:44.523
Actually...

03:44.525 --> 03:48.327
I came here to<i> win</i>
the Battle of the Bands.

03:48.329 --> 03:50.329
[ Gasps ]

03:50.331 --> 03:52.731
[ Bass playing chords ]

03:52.733 --> 03:54.066
My bad!

03:54.068 --> 03:55.667
Dude, what gives?!

03:55.669 --> 03:57.402
I thought you gave me this
guitar so<i> I</i> could win.

03:57.404 --> 04:00.005
Ha.
I didn't give it to you.

04:00.007 --> 04:03.742
In fact, it's time for you
to pay up, Buttercup.

04:03.744 --> 04:06.178
Pay up?!
I don't have any money!

04:06.180 --> 04:08.280
Buttercup, what's going on?

04:08.282 --> 04:09.781
Oh, I don't need money.

04:09.783 --> 04:12.017
All I need is a drummer...
[ snaps fingers ]

04:12.019 --> 04:14.152
[ Screams ]

04:16.590 --> 04:19.191
And a bassist.
[ Snaps fingers ]

04:19.193 --> 04:22.060
Buttercup!

04:22.062 --> 04:24.129
No strings attached, huh?

04:24.131 --> 04:26.298
Steve, what's going on here?

04:26.300 --> 04:28.533
Hey, man, you made a deal.

04:28.535 --> 04:29.968
I gave you the guitar,

04:29.970 --> 04:34.239
and now your sisters
are part of my band.

04:34.241 --> 04:38.243
[ High-pitched voice ] Forever!
[ Laughs maniacally ]

04:38.245 --> 04:41.380
[ Gasps ] Him!

04:41.382 --> 04:43.248
Oof!
[ Plays chord ]

04:43.250 --> 04:44.449
Ow.

04:44.451 --> 04:45.884
Ugh, dang it, Buttercup!

04:45.886 --> 04:48.420
I knew you did something bad
to get that guitar!

04:48.422 --> 04:50.555
All right, Blossom.

04:50.557 --> 04:52.090
You need to stop
and think things through

04:52.092 --> 04:54.092
before you rush to judgment.

04:54.094 --> 04:57.829
<i> Me</i> think things through?!
You were the one who --

04:57.831 --> 05:01.066
[ High-pitched voice ] If you're
going to be in<i> my</i> band,

05:01.068 --> 05:05.937
you're going to have to
sing like<i> me!</i>

05:05.939 --> 05:07.072
What are you...

05:07.074 --> 05:09.174
[ Zombie voice ]
...talking about?

05:09.176 --> 05:10.442
Leave us alone...

05:10.444 --> 05:12.444
[ Distorted voice ]
...you big meanie!

05:12.446 --> 05:13.679
[ Gasps ]

05:13.681 --> 05:17.082
Now, let's go win this,
Jampyres.

05:17.084 --> 05:22.287
[ Singsongy ] Ta-ta, Buttercup!
Enjoy your solo career.

05:22.289 --> 05:23.622
No!

05:23.624 --> 05:26.958
[ Laughs maniacally ]
Help us, Buttercup!

05:26.960 --> 05:28.260
Aw, Buttercup!

05:28.262 --> 05:30.295
This is the third to eighth
stupidest thing

05:30.297 --> 05:32.164
you've ever done.

05:32.166 --> 05:33.465
What was I thinking?

05:33.467 --> 05:36.101
Not much, apparently.

05:36.103 --> 05:38.837
[ Sighs ]

05:38.839 --> 05:41.840
♪ Never surrender ♪

05:41.842 --> 05:43.108
Yeah!

05:43.110 --> 05:46.478
Time to handle<i> this</i>
like a real rock star!

05:46.480 --> 05:48.447
Audience:
Rock, rock, rock, rock!

05:48.449 --> 05:50.048
[ Cheering ]

05:50.050 --> 05:53.785
[ Rock song begins ]

05:53.787 --> 05:58.023
[ High-pitched voice ]
We are the Jampyres!

05:58.025 --> 06:02.127
Prepare to have your socks
rocked off!

06:02.129 --> 06:04.129
[ Laughs ]

06:04.131 --> 06:05.864
Yo, claw hands!

06:05.866 --> 06:10.669
Thrash would never abandon her
bandmates, and neither will I.

06:10.671 --> 06:14.373
I challenge you to a rock-off!

06:14.375 --> 06:16.641
How delightful!

06:16.643 --> 06:18.477
What's the wager?

06:18.479 --> 06:21.146
If I win,
I get my sisters back.

06:21.148 --> 06:26.485
But if I win, you have to join
my band forever!

06:26.487 --> 06:28.487
Let's do it.

06:28.489 --> 06:30.722
♪ Rock off ♪

06:36.530 --> 06:38.063
[ Grunts ]

06:41.368 --> 06:44.669
[ Playing rock progression ]

06:49.410 --> 06:52.744
[ Solos playing concurrently ]

06:56.683 --> 06:59.684
[ Shrieking ]

06:59.686 --> 07:01.286
♪♪

07:01.288 --> 07:02.821
[ Gasps ]

07:05.559 --> 07:09.561
[ Laughing evilly ]

07:09.563 --> 07:11.696
[ Screams ]

07:11.698 --> 07:13.598
[ Squeaking ]

07:13.600 --> 07:15.567
[ Tires squeal ]

07:15.569 --> 07:18.537
[ Roars ]

07:18.539 --> 07:20.038
[ Flames whoosh ]

07:20.040 --> 07:21.406
[ Squeaks ]

07:21.408 --> 07:25.043
♪♪

07:25.045 --> 07:26.278
Aah!

07:26.280 --> 07:28.246
♪♪

07:28.248 --> 07:30.549
[ Blade zings ]

07:30.551 --> 07:33.585
[ Roars ]

07:33.587 --> 07:34.953
[ Explosion ]

07:34.955 --> 07:38.557
Uhh!
Ooh, nice try, little fry.

07:38.559 --> 07:40.659
[ Laughs evilly ]
[ Grunting ]

07:40.661 --> 07:42.761
[ Strained voice ]
His metal is strong.

07:42.763 --> 07:46.164
Only one thing left to do!

07:46.166 --> 07:48.400
This is for you, Thrash!

07:48.402 --> 07:51.136
[ Yells ]

07:51.138 --> 07:55.140
[ Playing solo ]

07:55.142 --> 07:58.009
[ Zombie voice ]
That's incredible!

07:58.011 --> 08:01.613
♪♪

08:01.615 --> 08:05.183
Very good!

08:05.185 --> 08:08.320
♪♪

08:11.692 --> 08:12.991
[ Twinkling sound ]

08:12.993 --> 08:15.193
[ Zombie voice ]
Buttercup!

08:15.195 --> 08:17.863
Well! I guess I win!

08:17.865 --> 08:20.765
Okay, Jampyres,
back to the --

08:20.767 --> 08:25.437
Whoa,
pretty fireball of doom!

08:25.439 --> 08:29.674
♪♪

08:29.676 --> 08:32.043
Time to finish this.

08:32.045 --> 08:36.515
♪♪

08:36.517 --> 08:40.852
Thank you, Townsville!

08:44.324 --> 08:49.794
That's the most metal thing
I've ever seen!

08:49.796 --> 08:53.865
[ Explosion ]

08:53.867 --> 08:58.737
[ Laughing maniacally ]

08:58.739 --> 09:01.406
[ Crowd cheering ]

09:01.408 --> 09:04.843
Buttercup! Buttercup! Buttercup!

09:04.845 --> 09:06.311
[ Cheering ]

09:06.313 --> 09:07.746
Buttercup, you did it!

09:07.748 --> 09:11.816
Yeah, but I'm sorry I sold
your souls for rock and roll.

09:11.818 --> 09:14.653
[ Zombie voice ]
Oh, it's okay.

09:14.655 --> 09:18.056
Um, Bubbles, you don't have
to do that voice anymore.

09:18.058 --> 09:20.825
[ Normal voice ] Oh!
Can we band battle now?

09:20.827 --> 09:23.828
Guys, I smashed my guitar...
again!

09:23.830 --> 09:25.730
Now we can't play at all!

09:25.732 --> 09:27.265
[ Growls ]

09:27.267 --> 09:29.401
Valhalla, yeah, you can!

09:29.403 --> 09:32.504
[ Rock guitar playing ]

09:36.543 --> 09:38.209
'Sup?

09:38.211 --> 09:39.678
Whoa, Thrash!

09:39.680 --> 09:42.047
You truly are a god of rock.

09:42.049 --> 09:46.518
I prefer goddess of rock.

09:46.520 --> 09:49.588
[ Roars ]

09:49.590 --> 09:52.924
[ Playing metal solo ]

09:52.926 --> 09:55.527
That's the most metal thing
I have ever seen.

09:55.529 --> 10:00.065
My bodacious Buttercup,
by putting your butt on the line

10:00.067 --> 10:02.367
and sacrificing the sickest
of guitars

10:02.369 --> 10:04.369
to save your rad sisters,

10:04.371 --> 10:08.306
you have earned some serious
rock star cred.

10:08.308 --> 10:11.376
And since you learned to be
righteously responsible,

10:11.378 --> 10:16.247
the Guild of Rock Gods would
like to present you with this!

10:16.249 --> 10:18.383
[ Screeches ]

10:18.385 --> 10:19.884
Here ya go, bud.

10:19.886 --> 10:21.920
It's a necronium diamond guitar.

10:21.922 --> 10:24.589
Hardcore unbreakable.

10:24.591 --> 10:25.890
Unbreakable?!

10:25.892 --> 10:29.494
Ha ha, yeah!
Believe me, I've tried.

10:29.496 --> 10:30.895
Thanks, Thrash.

10:30.897 --> 10:33.632
Play it most excellently.

10:33.634 --> 10:35.634
[ Imitating guitar solos ]

10:35.636 --> 10:40.905
Now it's time for this
goddess of rock...to roll.

10:40.907 --> 10:42.474
Bye!
Thank you!

10:42.476 --> 10:44.576
Bye!

10:44.578 --> 10:47.746
[ Engine sputtering ]

10:47.748 --> 10:49.748
[ Engine turns over ]

10:49.750 --> 10:51.850
All right,
you're good to go, bro.

10:51.852 --> 10:53.752
[ Tires squeal ]
See, Bloss?

10:53.754 --> 10:55.920
It always pays
to think things through.

10:55.922 --> 10:58.657
What,<i> what?!</i>
You were the one who --

10:58.659 --> 11:01.393
One, two, three, puppies!

11:03.530 --> 11:05.096
♪ Powerpuff Girls
fighting crime ♪ Yeah!

11:05.098 --> 11:06.631
♪ Saving the world
before bedtime ♪ Whoa!

11:06.633 --> 11:09.467
♪ Battling evil toe-to-toe ♪
Oh, no!

11:09.469 --> 11:14.072
♪ Saving the day,
a Powerpuff goal ♪
